nts2.d:
If you ever need some creative inspiration, take a look at some videos of Timbaland in the studio in his prime, around the early to mid-2000s. You'll see Timbo smiling knowingly as he plays new material to some of the biggest rap & R&B stars of all time, all of whom appear to display a similar range of emotions – confusion, astonishment, befuddled laughter. 
This is testament to the Virginia producer's utterly genre shifting approach to the rhythm and texture of beat-making. No one sounded like him before, and the many who have imitated rarely reach his level. 
This In Focus is selected by Antonine Scali.
Música sentimental for all the sad girls and sad boys.

An improvised set exploring different instruments and the acoustics of the space at the Wonder Cabinet in Bethlehem, Palestine."_
Broken club, dubbed out sounds, experimental electronics and atonal drifts: Gio’s monthly broadcasts are high contrast assemblages that move at a slow pace.
DJ PK, an alias of mysterious Leicester based producer brings his shadowy take on UK bass and experimental electronic music to the airwaves.

Monthly mixes and "Bad behaviour" from the crew behind Berlin's acclaimed Mala Junta parties. Expect throwback trance, souped up '90s basslines and party music of a high tempo flavour.
From the host: "LSDXOXO, draws us into his singular universe for an irresistible ride, full of bold suprises, boundless beats and delicious brilliance!"
A radio show curated by Surf Gang Records.

nts2.n: HIT A LICK RADIO W/ SLEEPWALKER ENTERTAINMENT
nts2.d:
Chester, PA’s DJ FINNAHITALICK (Blackwealth in the club) is a seasoned sound archivist of Underground Hip-hop. Starting Hit A Lick Radio in 2016, DJ FINNAHITALICK explores rap’s extensive subgenres and regional epicenters, ranging from DMV crank and Atlanta Plugg to Milwaukee low-end, Michigan punch-rap and beyond. His fast-paced mixes encapsulate Underground Hip-hop’s diverse landscape, and are not for the weak-hearted.
From the host: "A special 2015 archives set with Sleepwalker Entertainment out of Philadelphia, Pennsylvania"

nts2.n: KRISTIN KONTROL PRESENTS: OUT OF VOGUE

subtle.d: In:flux Audio are a record label based in Leeds, UK founded by production duo Tik&Borrow. Since the label's inception in October 2013, they have dabbled in multiple dance music styles with the emphasis always being on the tracks being unique, and packed full of bass. Today the primary output for the label is from their Dubstep roster and this is focus of their show on Subtle - giving the artists and remixers chance to showcase their sounds with an hour guest mix, all hosted by label bossman Tik.

I’m a 19 year old DJ and producer from Newcastle upon Tyne, mainly playing and producing music around the 140bpm mark. I started out playing old 2-step and jungle records, before moving my focus to mainly dubstep and grime. Along with my friends Pirata and White Label, I run Newcastle’s only current 140 night, Well Irie.
